        <briefdescription>
<para>Looks up the device configuration based on the unique device ID/BaseAddress. </para>        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>The XSpi_ConfigTable[] contains the configuration info for each device in the system.</para><para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>BaseAddress</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>contains the base address of the device</para></parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para>A pointer to the configuration found or NULL if the specified device ID/BaseAddress was not found. See <ref refid="xspi_8h" kindref="compound">xspi.h</ref> for the definition of <ref refid="struct_x_spi___config" kindref="compound">XSpi_Config</ref>.</para></simplesect>
<simplesect kind="note"><para>In XSCT/classic flow, DeviceId is used to look up the device configuration. </para></simplesect>
</para>        </detaileddescription>
